Types of class
--------------------
POM        #page      (depends on number of web pagsin the application)
TestClass  #TestCases (depends on no of testcases)

100MTC     -MAIN CLICK RUN 100 TIMES to Avoid we go for TestNG


Unit Testing Tool TestNG - Junit

In selenium we use TestNG to
1. Run Multiple Test Class
2. Result

We can install TestNG using market palace in selenium

Configuring Java Project
right click on java project -
go to build path
Select add libraries
select TestNG -> click Next -> Click Finish


TESTNG
1.It is a Test class which contains methods developed using Test Annotation
2. In TestNG Class we do not use main Method
3.To Print the message we use Reporter.log("Demo"); , Instead of System.out.println("Demo");
4.if you execute the TestNG Class it is automatically generate Test-Output folder(Emailable report.html file) Refresh java project

5.To run multiple Test class we use testng.xml -suite file
6.to create a suite file
a.right click on java project -> go to testng
b. select convert to testng > click finish


To run:
----------
right click on testng.xml -> RunAs TestNG

@DataProvider
@BeforeSuite
@Test
@BeforeTest
@BeforeClass
@BeforeMethod
@AfterMethod
@AfterClass
@AfterTest
@AfterSuite

@Parameters
@Optional
@Factory
@Listners

Default Execution Order of Annotation

1.@BeforeSuite
2.@BeforeTest
3.@BeforeClass
4.@BeforeMethod
5.@Test
6.@AfterMethod
7.@AfterClass
8.@AfterTest
9.@AfterSuite


Question:
-------------------

what is the difference between @Beforetest and @BeforeMethod

BeforeTest - is Exceuted Before Every Test Block present in testng.xml
BeforeMethod - is Exceuted Before Every Test method @Test) present in the TestNG Class



























